@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@samp{ebib-extras.el} extends @samp{ebib}, the Emacs Bib@TeX{} database manager, with a comprehensive set of commands for managing bibliographic entries and their associated files. Where @samp{ebib} provides a solid foundation for editing Bib@TeX{} databases, @samp{ebib-extras.el} adds the workflows that tie an entry to the broader research ecosystem: downloading PDFs by DOI or ISBN, attaching and renaming files to match entry keys, searching for works on external websites, setting ratings, writing PDF metadata, and keeping databases automatically saved and reloaded.

The package depends on several external packages and tools. @samp{el-patch} is used to modify core @samp{ebib} functions for better window management and timestamp handling. @samp{annas-archive} provides book downloading via Anna's Archive. @samp{paths} supplies the directory and file path constants that the library relies on. @samp{shut-up} suppresses noisy messages during batch operations. Additional optional integrations include @samp{eww-extras} for URL-to-file conversion, @samp{zotra-extras} for fetching field values via Zotero translators, @samp{files-extras} for OCR, @samp{citar} for note management, and the @samp{bib} package for identifier lookups.

The capabilities of the package can be organized into several thematic areas:

@itemize
@item
@strong{File handling and attachment.} Commands to open, attach, rename, and validate files associated with entries (@ref{File handling and attachment}).
@item
@strong{Entry processing.} A unified workflow for generating keys, setting languages, and attaching files to newly created entries (@ref{Entry processing and field manipulation}).
@item
@strong{External searching.} DWIM search commands that open browser tabs on Library Genesis, Google Scholar, Goodreads, IMDb, and many other websites (@ref{External searching}).
@item
@strong{Downloading.} Commands that download PDFs, HTML files, subtitles, and videos from various sources and attach them to entries (@ref{Downloading and attaching from external sources}).
@item
@strong{Database management.} Automatic saving, reloading, sorting, and navigation (@ref{Database management}).
@item
@strong{Patched functions.} Modifications to core @samp{ebib} functions using @samp{el-patch} (@ref{Patched functions}).
@end itemize

