@node DWIM attachment
@subsection DWIM attachment

@findex ebib-extras-attach-files
The command @code{ebib-extras-attach-files} is a DWIM command that tries to download and attach the most appropriate file for the entry at point (or a specified key). If the @samp{file} field is already non-empty, it simply calls @code{ebib-extras-set-abstract} to fill in the abstract. Otherwise, it checks for available identifiers and entry type in the following order:

@enumerate
@item
If a DOI is available, it calls @code{ebib-extras-doi-attach}.
@item
If an ISBN is available or the entry type is book-like, it calls @code{ebib-extras-book-attach}.
@item
If the URL matches a known video website (YouTube), it calls @code{ebib-extras-url-to-srt-attach} to download subtitles.
@item
If the entry type contains ``online'' and a URL is available, it calls both @code{ebib-extras-url-to-pdf-attach} and @code{ebib-extras-url-to-html-attach}.
@end enumerate

@node DOI and book attachment
@subsection DOI and book attachment

@findex ebib-extras-doi-attach
@findex ebib-extras-book-attach
The command @code{ebib-extras-doi-attach} downloads a PDF using the entry's DOI via @code{annas-archive-download}. It sets up a one-shot hook on @code{annas-archive-post-download-hook} to automatically attach the downloaded file once the download completes.

The command @code{ebib-extras-book-attach} searches for and downloads a book by ISBN or title via @code{annas-archive-download}. It prompts the user with a search string pre-filled from the entry's ISBN (if available) or title (for book-like entry types). Like @code{ebib-extras-doi-attach}, it uses a one-shot hook on @code{annas-archive-post-download-hook} to attach the file when the download finishes. If the download was initiated externally (not through @samp{eww}), it displays a message asking the user to attach the file manually.

@node URL-based file generation
@subsection URL-based file generation

@findex ebib-extras-url-to-pdf-attach
@findex ebib-extras-url-to-html-attach
@findex ebib-extras-url-to-srt-attach
The command @code{ebib-extras-url-to-pdf-attach} generates a PDF from the URL in the entry's @samp{url} field using @code{eww-extras-url-to-file} and attaches it to the entry once the conversion completes (via callback).

The command @code{ebib-extras-url-to-html-attach} works the same way but generates an HTML file instead.

The command @code{ebib-extras-url-to-srt-attach} downloads subtitles for the URL in the entry's @samp{url} field using an external command (formatted by @code{eww-extras-download-subtitles}, typically @samp{yt-dlp}). The subtitles are downloaded to the downloads directory, but unlike the other commands in this group, the resulting file must be attached manually.

@node Downloading PDFs and videos
@subsection Downloading PDFs and videos

@findex ebib-extras-download-pdf
@findex ebib-extras-download-video
The command @code{ebib-extras-download-pdf} attempts to download a PDF of the work at point by trying multiple strategies in order: first by DOI (via @code{annas-archive-download}), then by URL (via @code{eww-extras-url-to-pdf}), and finally by ISBN (via @code{ebib-extras-download-book}). It works in both @code{ebib-entry-mode} and @code{bibtex-mode}.

The command @code{ebib-extras-download-video} downloads a video using @samp{yt-dlp}. It requires @samp{yt-dlp} to be installed (signals a user error otherwise). The video is saved to the media library directory with the entry's key as the filename (with @samp{.webm} extension), and the @samp{file} field is updated. The download runs asynchronously via @code{async-shell-command}.

@node Downloading by title
@subsection Downloading by title

@findex ebib-extras-download-book-by-title
@findex ebib-extras-download-article-by-title
The command @code{ebib-extras-download-book-by-title} opens the entry's title on multiple download-oriented websites defined in @code{ebib-extras-download-book-functions}, which includes Goodreads, HathiTrust, UC Berkeley library, Internet Archive, Library Genesis, Audible, and Audiobook Bay.

The command @code{ebib-extras-download-article-by-title} opens the entry's title on websites defined in @code{ebib-extras-download-article-functions}. The aliases @code{ebib-extras-download-film-by-title} and @code{ebib-extras-download-film-by-identifier} both point to @code{ebib-extras-search-film-by-title} because there is no separate download path for films.

@node Database management
@section Database management

@menu
