@node Sort states
@section Sort states

@vindex ebib-extras-sort-states
@vindex ebib-extras-sort-state
The constant @code{ebib-extras-sort-states} defines the available sorting criteria for the Ebib index buffer as a list of symbols: @code{(Timestamp Author Title)}.

The variable @code{ebib-extras-sort-state} holds the current sorting criterion and is advanced to the next state each time @code{ebib-extras-sort} is called (@ref{Sorting}).

@node Entry type constants
@section Entry type constants

@vindex ebib-extras-book-like-entry-types
@vindex ebib-extras-article-like-entry-types
@vindex ebib-extras-film-like-entry-types
The constant @code{ebib-extras-book-like-entry-types} lists Bib@TeX{} entry types considered as books or book-like entities: @samp{book}, @samp{collection}, @samp{mvbook}, @samp{inbook}, @samp{incollection}, @samp{bookinbook}, and @samp{suppbook} (both lowercase and capitalized forms). This list is used by @code{ebib-extras-get-supertype} and by commands that dispatch based on entry type (@ref{ISBN and entry type detection}).

The constant @code{ebib-extras-article-like-entry-types} lists entry types considered as articles: @samp{article} (both cases).

The constant @code{ebib-extras-film-like-entry-types} lists entry types considered as films: @samp{movie}, @samp{video}, and @samp{tvepisode} (both cases).

@node File extension constants
@section File extension constants

@vindex ebib-extras-valid-file-extensions
@vindex ebib-extras-valid-text-file-extensions
The constant @code{ebib-extras-valid-file-extensions} defines the preference order for opening files: @samp{("pdf" "html" "webm" "flac" "mp3" "md" "srt" "vtt")}. This is used by @code{ebib-extras-open-file-dwim} to determine which file to open when multiple are attached (@ref{Opening associated files}).

The constant @code{ebib-extras-valid-text-file-extensions} defines extensions considered as text files: @samp{("html" "pdf" "srt" "vtt")}. This is used by @code{ebib-extras-get-text-file} to find the first text file associated with an entry (@ref{File retrieval}).

@node Key validation pattern
@section Key validation pattern

@vindex ebib-extras-valid-key-regexp
The constant @code{ebib-extras-valid-key-regexp} defines the regular expression that valid Bib@TeX{} keys must match: alphanumeric characters and underscores/hyphens, at least two characters, followed by exactly four digits (a year), followed by at least two more alphanumeric characters. This pattern is used by @code{ebib-extras-key-is-valid-p} (@ref{Key validation}).

