@node Database constants
@section Database constants

@vindex ebib-extras-db-numbers
@vindex ebib-extras-auto-save-files
The constant @code{ebib-extras-db-numbers} is an association list mapping database file paths to their numeric identifiers. It associates the personal bibliography files and Tlon project files with numbers 1 through 5.

The constant @code{ebib-extras-auto-save-files} lists database files that should participate in auto-saving. By default, it includes the new personal bibliography and the Tlon fluid bibliography. Larger files containing older entries are excluded to avoid frequent writes.

@node Invalid file tracking
@section Invalid file tracking

@vindex ebib-extras-invalid-files
@vindex ebib-extras-file-notify-descriptors
@vindex ebib-extras-last-reload-times
The variable @code{ebib-extras-invalid-files} holds the list of invalidly named files found by @code{ebib-extras-list-invalid-files} (@ref{Managing invalid files}). Each element is a file path whose base name does not correspond to a known Bib@TeX{} key.

The variable @code{ebib-extras-file-notify-descriptors} holds the list of active file-notify descriptors for auto-reloading databases. These are used by @code{ebib-extras-remove-file-notify-watchers} to clean up watchers.

The variable @code{ebib-extras-last-reload-times} is a hash table mapping database file paths to their last reload time, used for the cooldown mechanism in the auto-reload callback (@ref{Saving and reloading databases}).

@node Author tracking
@section Author tracking

@vindex ebib-extras-existing-authors
The variable @code{ebib-extras-existing-authors} holds the list of all authors in the current database, populated by @code{ebib-extras-create-list-of-existing-authors}. It is used by @code{ebib-extras-check-author-exists} to verify that an author already appears in the database (@ref{Author checking}).

@node Patched functions
@chapter Patched functions

@samp{ebib-extras.el} modifies several core @samp{ebib} functions using @samp{el-patch}. These patches address specific usability issues and edge cases in the default behavior.

@menu
* @code{ebib--setup-windows}::
* @code{ebib--store-entry}::
* @code{ebib-reload-current-database}::
* @code{ebib-edit-entry}::
* @code{ebib-copy-field-contents}::
@end menu

@node @code{ebib--setup-windows}
@section @code{ebib--setup-windows}

@findex ebib--setup-windows
The patch to @code{ebib--setup-windows} prevents unnecessary vertical window splits when opening Ebib. In the original implementation, Ebib always splits the selected window to show both the index and entry buffers. The patched version reuses the selected window for the entry buffer instead of splitting, resulting in a less disruptive layout. The patch also removes the dedication of the index window, allowing it to be reused by other commands.

@node @code{ebib--store-entry}
@section @code{ebib--store-entry}

@findex ebib--store-entry
The patch to @code{ebib--store-entry} adds a @samp{"GMT"} timezone argument to the @code{format-time-string} call when creating timestamps. This ensures that all timestamps in the bibliography are recorded in UTC, providing consistency regardless of the user's local timezone.

@node @code{ebib-reload-current-database}
@section @code{ebib-reload-current-database}

@findex ebib-reload-current-database
The patch to @code{ebib-reload-current-database} wraps the buffer update step in @code{save-window-excursion}, preventing point from jumping to an unexpected position after reloading. Without this patch, the window configuration can shift when @samp{ebib} updates its buffers.

@node @code{ebib-edit-entry}
@section @code{ebib-edit-entry}

@findex ebib-edit-entry
The patch to @code{ebib-edit-entry} adds a workaround for an edge case where pressing @samp{RET} in @code{ebib-index-mode} with point on the first line of the buffer would fail to select the correct entry. The patch moves point to the next entry and back (or to the previous entry and back) to force the selection to update before calling @code{ebib--edit-entry-internal}.

@node @code{ebib-copy-field-contents}
@section @code{ebib-copy-field-contents}

@findex ebib-copy-field-contents
The patch to @code{ebib-copy-field-contents} changes the behavior when the field contains a file path. Instead of copying the potentially abbreviated path stored in the @samp{file} field, the patched version expands it to the absolute, true file path (using @code{file-truename}) before copying to the kill ring. Non-file values are copied unchanged.

